{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1000,"text":"\"When the crisis came,"},{"time":3261,"text":"the serious limitations\nof existing economic and financial models"},{"time":7971,"text":"immediately became apparent.\""},{"time":12195,"text":"\"There is also a strong belief,\nwhich I share,"},{"time":16373,"text":"that bad or oversimplistic\nand overconfident economics"},{"time":21361,"text":"helped create the crisis.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":23290,"text":"Now, you've probably all heard\nof similar criticism"},{"time":25871,"text":"coming from people\nwho are skeptical of capitalism."},{"time":29546,"text":"But this is different."},{"time":30741,"text":"This is coming from the heart of finance."},{"time":34444,"text":"The first quote\nis from Jean-Claude Trichet"},{"time":37368,"text":"when he was governor\nof the European Central Bank."},{"time":41180,"text":"The second quote is from the head\nof the UK Financial Services Authority."},{"time":47015,"text":"Are these people implying"},{"time":48586,"text":"that we don't understand\nthe economic systems"},{"time":51350,"text":"that drive our modern societies?"},{"time":54519,"text":"It gets worse."},{"time":56444,"text":"\"We spend billions of dollars"},{"time":58657,"text":"trying to understand\nthe origins of the universe,"},{"time":62643,"text":"while we still don't understand\nthe conditions for a stable society,"},{"time":68537,"text":"a functioning economy, or peace.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":74177,"text":"What's happening here?\nHow can this be possible?"},{"time":76973,"text":"Do we really understand more\nabout the fabric of reality"},{"time":80244,"text":"than we do about the fabric\nwhich emerges from our human interactions?"},{"time":84730,"text":"Unfortunately, the answer is yes."},{"time":87257,"text":"But there's an intriguing solution"},{"time":89998,"text":"which is coming from what is known\nas the science of complexity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":95785,"text":"To explain what this means\nand what this thing is,"},{"time":98496,"text":"please let me quickly take\na couple of steps back."},{"time":101971,"text":"I ended up in physics by accident."},{"time":104213,"text":"It was a random encounter\nwhen I was young,"},{"time":107351,"text":"and since then, I've often wondered\nabout the amazing success of physics"},{"time":111969,"text":"in describing the reality\nwe wake up in every day."},{"time":116141,"text":"In a nutshell, you can think\nof physics as follows."},{"time":118904,"text":"So you take a chunk of reality\nyou want to understand"},{"time":122522,"text":"and you translate it into mathematics."},{"time":126151,"text":"You encode it into equations."},{"time":129142,"text":"Then, predictions can be made and tested."},{"time":133124,"text":"We're actually\nreally lucky that this works,"},{"time":135636,"text":"because no one really knows\nwhy the thoughts in our heads"},{"time":138548,"text":"should actually relate to the fundamental\nworkings of the universe."},{"time":144278,"text":"Despite the success,\nphysics has its limits."},{"time":147688,"text":"As Dirk Helbing pointed out\nin the last quote,"},{"time":150762,"text":"we don't really understand the complexity\nthat relates to us, that surrounds us."},{"time":156601,"text":"This paradox is what got me interested\nin complex systems."},{"time":160729,"text":"So these are systems which are made up"},{"time":162629,"text":"of many interconnected\nor interacting parts:"},{"time":166113,"text":"swarms of birds or fish,"},{"time":168946,"text":"ant colonies, ecosystems,\nbrains, financial markets."},{"time":173521,"text":"These are just a few examples."}]},{"cues":[{"time":177687,"text":"Interestingly, complex systems\nare very hard to map"},{"time":182930,"text":"into mathematical equations,"},{"time":184953,"text":"so the usual physics approach\ndoesn't really work here."},{"time":189283,"text":"So what do we know about complex systems?"},{"time":191476,"text":"Well, it turns out that what looks\nlike complex behavior from the outside"},{"time":197532,"text":"is actually the result\nof a few simple rules of interaction."},{"time":202995,"text":"This means you can forget\nabout the equations"},{"time":206859,"text":"and just start to understand the system"},{"time":209609,"text":"by looking at the interactions,"},{"time":211352,"text":"so you can actually forget\nabout the equations"},{"time":213746,"text":"and you just start to look\nat the interactions."},{"time":216322,"text":"And it gets even better,\nbecause most complex systems"},{"time":219680,"text":"have this amazing property\ncalled emergence."},{"time":222698,"text":"So this means that the system as a whole\nsuddenly starts to show a behavior"},{"time":226913,"text":"which cannot be understood or predicted"},{"time":229809,"text":"by looking at the components\nof the system."},{"time":232386,"text":"So the whole is literally\nmore than the sum of its parts."},{"time":236659,"text":"And all of this also means"},{"time":237957,"text":"that you can forget about\nthe individual parts of the system,"},{"time":242845,"text":"how complex they are."},{"time":244190,"text":"So if it's a cell or a termite or a bird,"},{"time":249202,"text":"you just focus on the rules\nof interaction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253950,"text":"As a result, networks are ideal\nrepresentations of complex systems."},{"time":261102,"text":"The nodes in the network\nare the system's components,"},{"time":266849,"text":"and the links are given\nby the interactions."},{"time":270614,"text":"So what equations are for physics,"},{"time":272917,"text":"complex networks are for the study\nof complex systems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":277664,"text":"This approach has been\nvery successfully applied"},{"time":280898,"text":"to many complex systems\nin physics, biology,"},{"time":284516,"text":"computer science, the social sciences,"},{"time":287260,"text":"but what about economics?"},{"time":289557,"text":"Where are economic networks?"},{"time":292113,"text":"This is a surprising\nand prominent gap in the literature."},{"time":296983,"text":"The study we published last year, called\n\"The Network of Global Corporate Control,\""},{"time":302837,"text":"was the first extensive analysis\nof economic networks."},{"time":308654,"text":"The study went viral on the Internet"},{"time":311240,"text":"and it attracted a lot of attention\nfrom the international media."},{"time":316246,"text":"This is quite remarkable, because, again,\nwhy did no one look at this before?"},{"time":320489,"text":"Similar data has been\naround for quite some time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":323572,"text":"What we looked at in detail\nwas ownership networks."},{"time":329070,"text":"So here the nodes are companies,\npeople, governments, foundations, etc."},{"time":336124,"text":"And the links represent\nthe shareholding relations,"},{"time":339032,"text":"so shareholder A has x percent\nof the shares in company B."},{"time":344220,"text":"And we also assign a value to the company\ngiven by the operating revenue."},{"time":349778,"text":"So ownership networks reveal the patterns\nof shareholding relations."},{"time":356045,"text":"In this little example,\nyou can see a few financial institutions"},{"time":360194,"text":"with some of the many links highlighted."}]},{"cues":[{"time":363845,"text":"Now, you may think that no one\nlooked at this before"},{"time":366714,"text":"because ownership networks\nare really, really boring to study."},{"time":371941,"text":"Well, as ownership is related to control,"},{"time":376031,"text":"as I shall explain later,"},{"time":377588,"text":"looking at ownership networks"},{"time":379029,"text":"actually can give you\nanswers to questions like,"},{"time":381731,"text":"who are the key players?"},{"time":383204,"text":"How are they organized?\nAre they isolated?"},{"time":385554,"text":"Are they interconnected?"},{"time":387223,"text":"And what is the overall\ndistribution of control?"},{"time":391153,"text":"In other words, who controls the world?"},{"time":394415,"text":"I think this is an interesting question."}]},{"cues":[{"time":396781,"text":"And it has implications for systemic risk."},{"time":401348,"text":"This is a measure of how vulnerable\na system is overall."},{"time":406862,"text":"A high degree of interconnectivity\ncan be bad for stability,"},{"time":411524,"text":"because then the stress can spread\nthrough the system like an epidemic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":418332,"text":"Scientists have sometimes\ncriticized economists"},{"time":420889,"text":"who believe ideas and concepts\nare more important than empirical data,"},{"time":426420,"text":"because a foundational\nguideline in science is:"},{"time":429958,"text":"Let the data speak. OK. Let's do that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":432615,"text":"So we started with a database containing\n13 million ownership relations from 2007."},{"time":439581,"text":"This is a lot of data,\nand because we wanted to find out"},{"time":442892,"text":"\"who rules the world,\""},{"time":445024,"text":"we decided to focus\non transnational corporations,"},{"time":448452,"text":"or \"TNCs,\" for short."},{"time":449800,"text":"These are companies that operate\nin more than one country,"},{"time":453396,"text":"and we found 43,000."},{"time":457148,"text":"In the next step, we built\nthe network around these companies,"},{"time":460133,"text":"so we took all the TNCs' shareholders,"},{"time":462513,"text":"and the shareholders' shareholders, etc.,"},{"time":464496,"text":"all the way upstream,\nand we did the same downstream,"},{"time":467372,"text":"and ended up with a network\ncontaining 600,000 nodes"},{"time":471524,"text":"and one million links."},{"time":473310,"text":"This is the TNC network which we analyzed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":477251,"text":"And it turns out to be\nstructured as follows."},{"time":479384,"text":"So you have a periphery and a center"},{"time":481935,"text":"which contains about 75 percent\nof all the players,"},{"time":486939,"text":"and in the center,\nthere's this tiny but dominant core"},{"time":491014,"text":"which is made up of highly\ninterconnected companies."},{"time":495116,"text":"To give you a better picture,"},{"time":497406,"text":"think about a metropolitan area."},{"time":499071,"text":"So you have the suburbs and the periphery,"},{"time":501101,"text":"you have a center,\nlike a financial district,"},{"time":503958,"text":"then the core will be something like"},{"time":505708,"text":"the tallest high-rise building\nin the center."},{"time":509732,"text":"And we already see signs\nof organization going on here."},{"time":514350,"text":"36 percent of the TNCs\nare in the core only,"},{"time":519588,"text":"but they make up 95 percent of the total\noperating revenue of all TNCs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":526754,"text":"OK, so now we analyzed the structure,"},{"time":529380,"text":"so how does this relate to the control?"},{"time":533517,"text":"Well, ownership gives\nvoting rights to shareholders."},{"time":537187,"text":"This is the normal notion of control."},{"time":539961,"text":"And there are different models"},{"time":541453,"text":"which allow you to compute\nthe control you get from ownership."},{"time":545918,"text":"If you have more than 50 percent\nof the shares in a company,"},{"time":548766,"text":"you get control,"},{"time":550115,"text":"but usually, it depends\non the relative distribution of shares."},{"time":555092,"text":"And the network really matters."},{"time":558315,"text":"About 10 years ago, Mr. Tronchetti Provera"},{"time":561264,"text":"had ownership and control\nin a small company,"},{"time":564699,"text":"which had ownership and control\nin a bigger company."},{"time":567886,"text":"You get the idea."},{"time":569454,"text":"This ended up giving him control\nin Telecom Italia with a leverage of 26."},{"time":576490,"text":"So this means that,\nwith each euro he invested,"},{"time":579787,"text":"he was able to move 26 euros\nof market value"},{"time":583755,"text":"through the chain of ownership relations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":587175,"text":"Now what we actually computed in our study\nwas the control over the TNCs' value."},{"time":594035,"text":"This allowed us to assign\na degree of influence to each shareholder."},{"time":599765,"text":"This is very much in the sense\nof Max Weber's idea of potential power,"},{"time":604864,"text":"which is the probability\nof imposing one's own will"},{"time":608355,"text":"despite the opposition of others."}]},{"cues":[{"time":612406,"text":"If you want to compute the flow\nin an ownership network,"},{"time":617187,"text":"this is what you have to do."},{"time":618568,"text":"It's actually not that hard to understand."},{"time":620786,"text":"Let me explain by giving you this analogy."},{"time":623817,"text":"So think about water flowing in pipes,\nwhere the pipes have different thickness."},{"time":629591,"text":"So similarly, the control is flowing\nin the ownership networks"},{"time":634969,"text":"and is accumulating at the nodes."},{"time":639073,"text":"So what did we find after computing\nall this network control?"},{"time":643125,"text":"Well, it turns out\nthat the 737 top shareholders"},{"time":648510,"text":"have the potential to collectively control\n80 percent of the TNCs' value."},{"time":655728,"text":"Now remember, we started out\nwith 600,000 nodes,"},{"time":658457,"text":"so these 737 top players\nmake up a bit more than 0.1 percent."},{"time":666174,"text":"They're mostly financial institutions\nin the US and the UK."},{"time":671085,"text":"And it gets even more extreme."},{"time":674052,"text":"There are 146 top players in the core,"},{"time":678979,"text":"and they together have the potential\nto collectively control"},{"time":682205,"text":"40 percent of the TNCs' value."}]},{"cues":[{"time":688081,"text":"What should you take home\nfrom all of this?"},{"time":690379,"text":"Well, the high degree of control you saw\nis very extreme by any standard."},{"time":699285,"text":"The high degree of interconnectivity\nof the top players in the core"},{"time":704267,"text":"could pose a significant systemic risk\nto the global economy."},{"time":709960,"text":"And we could easily\nreproduce the TNC network"},{"time":712466,"text":"with a few simple rules."},{"time":714766,"text":"This means that its structure is probably\nthe result of self-organization."},{"time":718830,"text":"It's an emergent property which depends\non the rules of interaction in the system,"},{"time":724697,"text":"so it's probably not the result\nof a top-down approach"},{"time":728536,"text":"like a global conspiracy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":732099,"text":"Our study \"is an impression\nof the moon's surface."},{"time":734722,"text":"It's not a street map.\""},{"time":736055,"text":"So you should take the exact numbers\nin our study with a grain of salt,"},{"time":739889,"text":"yet it \"gave us a tantalizing glimpse\nof a brave new world of finance.\""},{"time":748188,"text":"We hope to have opened the door\nfor more such research in this direction,"},{"time":752241,"text":"so the remaining unknown terrain\nwill be charted in the future."},{"time":757036,"text":"And this is slowly starting."},{"time":758641,"text":"We're seeing the emergence of long-term\nand highly-funded programs"},{"time":763756,"text":"which aim at understanding\nour networked world"},{"time":767407,"text":"from a complexity point of view."},{"time":769861,"text":"But this journey has only just begun,"},{"time":771683,"text":"so we will have to wait\nbefore we see the first results."}]},{"cues":[{"time":777410,"text":"Now there is still\na big problem, in my opinion."},{"time":781541,"text":"Ideas relating to finance,\neconomics, politics, society,"},{"time":787490,"text":"are very often tainted\nby people's personal ideologies."},{"time":793448,"text":"I really hope that this\ncomplexity perspective"},{"time":797597,"text":"allows for some common ground to be found."},{"time":802977,"text":"It would be really great\nif it has the power"},{"time":805238,"text":"to help end the gridlock\ncreated by conflicting ideas,"},{"time":810391,"text":"which appears to be paralyzing\nour globalized world."},{"time":815572,"text":"Reality is so complex,\nwe need to move away from dogma."},{"time":820360,"text":"But this is just my own personal ideology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":822941,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":824116,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}